        "tm-eyebrow": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Breakfast</p>",
            "size": "sm",
            "uppercase": true,
            "muted": true,
            "position": "right"
          }
        },
        "tm-heading": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Fresh eggs, warm bread, the olives from our neighbor's tree.",
            "size": "5xl",
            "position": "right"
          }
        },
        "tm-body-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Breakfast is served on the stone terrace every morning from seven until ten. Whatever's ripe in the orchard, fresh bread we walk down for, eggs from the four hens we keep, yogurt and honey and fruit. No buffet. No schedule. Just what we'd make for ourselves.</p>",
            "size": "base",
            "uppercase": false,
            "muted": false,
            "position": "right"
          }
        },
        "tm-body-2": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>On windy days we serve inside the small dining room. On still days most guests stay out there until late morning, reading or drawing or just watching the light move.</p>",
            "size": "base",
            "uppercase": false,
            "muted": true,
            "position": "right"
          }
        }
      },
      "blocksOrder": [
        "tm-image",
        "tm-eyebrow",
        "tm-heading",
        "tm-body-1",
        "tm-body-2"
      ]
